Towards a quantitative representation of the cell signaling mechanisms of hallucinogens: Measurement and mathematical modeling of 5-HT1A and 5-HT2A receptor-mediated ERK1/2 activation

notes.body: to regenerate the PIP2, DAG is phosphorylated by DAG kinase (dgk) to produce phosphatidic acid (PA). CDP-DAG synthase (CDS*) adds on CMP to phosphatidic acid.This product DGP-DAG, is the activator donor of the phosphatidyl group to inositol. The PI is phosphorylated by PI kinase and PIP kinase to yield PIP2.
